> **TL;DR:** This repo is the **browser UI** for our college basketball RTS/sim.
>
> - **Map view:** PixiJS renders an interactive US map with traveling assistant coaches.
> - **UI shell:** Next.js (React, TypeScript, Tailwind).
> - **Realtime:** WebSocket to backend (Django/Channels). Server is authoritative; client is a renderer + command sender.
> - **State:** Zustand for client state; server diffs over WS hydrate/patch.

---

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js (App Router), React 18, TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS + CSS variables; shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) for controls
- **Canvas:** PixiJS for the map/RTS layer
- **State:** Zustand (lightweight store) + React Query (for REST)
- **Data:**
  - WebSocket (Channels) for `STATE_DIFF`/events and command acks
  - REST/GraphQL (TBD) for non-realtime pages (roster, budgets, settings)
- **Lint/Format:** ESLint, Prettier, Husky + lint-staged
- **Testing:** Vitest + React Testing Library, Playwright (e2e)
- **CI/CD:** (configure per repo; default GitHub Actions)

